WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.700 --> 00:00:08.200
Not every call is yours to close alone. And knowing when to hand off is part of doing the job well.

2
00:00:10.000 --> 00:00:20.233
Escalate immediately if a customer asks for a discount or a final price, mentions legal action, or needs custom dimensions.

3
00:00:22.033 --> 00:00:37.833
Escalate if they become upset after two objection attempts, ask about partnerships or bulk orders, ask about refunds, or ask something genuinely outside this training after two tries.

4
00:00:39.633 --> 00:00:54.067
Know your store map — Delhi, Mohali, Mumbai, Surat, with Bangalore and Hyderabad opening soon, plus Florida in the USA.

5
00:00:55.867 --> 00:01:04.567
If a customer's city isn't listed, offer a sample delivery or a video call instead — never 'we don't serve you.'

6
00:01:06.367 --> 00:01:09.333
And keep the five-second pitch ready.

7
00:01:11.133 --> 00:01:28.867
Magppie makes the world's first kitchens entirely from stone — zero wood, zero formaldehyde, zero termites — antibacterial, scratch-proof, with a twenty-five year guarantee and twenty-five annual services.

8
00:01:30.667 --> 00:01:35.567
Know when to hand off. It is part of doing the job well.

